they'll be looking at it, no word on a fix has yet come forth.<br><br>If you don't want the pet taking XP, get yourself a high-damage class in the group. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/uredgiki.showPublicProfile?language=EN>redgiki</A> at: 5/30/02 7:22:35 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/usurrpurr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SurrPurr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beastling</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#871F78>(5/31/02 8:11:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1720.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Experience with pet when group?</span><hr size=1> Fortunately, the quote redigiki posted was later repealed and is not correct. We need to stop this before this starts getting out of hand again! PETS ONLY TAKE EXP IF THEY OUT DAMAGE THE ENTIRE GROUP! After this quote was first published I had an even harder time finding groups, even the people who knew what I could do didn't want me because they didn't want me and my pet taking two shares of the exp. <br><br><br>Quote:<br>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>Hello.<br>I have an update, rather a correction, on one of the answers to the questions that the Mage Compendium folks sent in.<br><br>I was just informed by Scott Hartsman that I made a mistake about the pet experience thing. Pets only take experience from a group if they outdamage the entire group. If they do, then they gain a share as if they were a group member. If they do not, they take no experience at all.<br><br>This is how it's been working the whole time, and it makes a lot more sense. I'm sorry for the mistake.<br><br>Alan<br>--